<br>
Each NPC has a quest &quot;list&quot;. That quest list entries have:<br>
1) A required level (may be 1)<br>
2) A required faction level (may be dubious)<br>
3) A list of items, amount required and amount already in<br>
4) An amount of cash<br>
5) A text for &quot;I need more&quot;<br>
6) A reward (item, text, faction, xp, cash or all of the above)<br>
<br>
Note that, for NPC who has multiple quest, one restriction from the quest engine is that no item can ever be part of two quest entries. It's simply not possible.<br>
<br>
For every item or coin you hand in (coins are handled exactly as items, but come last), the NPC looks first the requirements: faction/level. If not, he'll ignore the handing. If ok, it looks thru the table above, and increments the count of items handled in. Then it checks for that quest entry &quot;are all the items in&quot;. If so, trigger #6 (reward). If not, trigger #5 (I need more). Note that's why, when handing 4 items, the NPC often asks for more 3 items in a row, then gives out the reward immediately: each slot in the give window works separately.<br>
<br>
The only way MQ fails is if 3 &amp; 4 are not satisfied, i.e. the NPC does not consider (yet) it has received the items/cash. And the only way #3 isn't complete is if:<br>
<br>
- The person handing an item didn't have the required level<br>
- The person handing an item didn't have the required faction<br>
- Or the person didn't hand the item yet<br>
<br>
There is no other reason why MQ fails. If you didn't get the item, it's one of the three above.<br>
<br>
Specially for something as straightforward as this quest, saying &quot;something bugged&quot; is weaseling out of the 3 reasons above. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 9:52:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4500.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Correct Way to MQ Velious Armor?</span><hr size=1> I've done MQ on totemic armor as well actually, by giving the npc the first items and logging in my alt to complete the quest.<br>
There isn't any set timer on quest hand ins as far as I know. Obviously when someone else gives something that's not part of the quest it will screw up the MQ. But If the npc isn't interrupted between items you can wait all day long if you want.<br>
I imagine because the bracer poofed it was a faction issue. If you had hit trade first and he hit it second then he should have received the bracer himself. There isn't any reason why the bracer shouldn't have shown up in one of your inventories if you both had ally faction and there wasn't anything traded to the npc in between.<br>
